			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of 22-year-old R.S. on her family who were deported in the summer of 1941 from Subcarpathia, her experiences in the
					ghetto of Tab (Western Hungary), slave labor outside the ghetto, deportation from Kaposvár, her experiences in Birkenau and forced
					labor in an ammunition factory in Lichtenau, a transport to Leipzig and a death march at the end of the war, and liberation in
					Wurtzen by US troops.</p>
			</abstract>
